  "texts": [
    "The test step (includes detecting anomaly and providing explanation) is typically seen to be under 1 millisecond per sensor.",
    "The time taken for training and pre-testing are linear to the number of records seen in the normal and attack datasets, respectively.For ECOD and Deep-SVDD in Mathuros et al. [12], the training time is shorter in comparison with GiBy.",
    "This is because they train approximately 24 minutes of data, i.e., 24 • 60 = 1440 records for each of the six process stages of SWaT; as opposed to the entire normal dataset of 495000 records trained by GiBy.",
    "ECOD detection time was reported to range from 0.72s to 4.62s, whereas for Deep-SVDD, it was 15.88s to 16.45s.",
    "Their Integrated Gradient (IG) XAI used with Deep-SVDD was the fastest with a time of 5.33s."
  ],
